    <section id="submitting">
      <h3>Submitting Data</h3>
      <section id="data-submission">
        <h4>Data Submission</h4>
        <pre><code>ssh-ed25519 AAAAC3Nza... Service.Key@LocalEGA</code></pre>
        <pre><code>crypt4gh encrypt --recipient_pk $lega_pubkey_file < $filename > $filename.c4gh</code></pre>
        <pre><code>sftp -o User=$username -P 2222 -i $privkey_file $lega_ip</code></pre>
      </section>

      <section id="metadata-submission">
        <h4>Metadata Submission</h4>
        <p>If the ingestion of the file succeeds, the user will be able to submit the metadata...</p>
      </section>

      <section id="encryption">
        <h4>Encryption & Backup</h4>
        <p>After the staging has been completed successfully, the file is re-encrypted...</p>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section id="access">
      <h3>Accessing Data</h3>
      <section id="sftp">
        <h4>SSH File Transfer Protocol</h4>
        <p>The most immediate way to download files from a LEGA node is by accessing its distribution endpoint using SFTP...</p>
      </section>

      <section id="quickview">
        <h4>EGA-QuickView</h4>
        <p>This tool takes advantage of Crypt4GH using block encryption and the fact that LEGA allows partial byte requests...</p>
      </section>
    </section>

    <section id="create-node">
      <h3>Can I Create a Node?</h3>
      <p>Yes, it is possible to create a FEGA Portugal node in your own institution...</p>

      <section id="advantages">
        <h4>Advantages</h4>
        <p>This can be suited for institutions with very strict data policies...</p>
      </section>

      <section id="responsibilities">
        <h4>Responsibilities</h4>
        <p>You have to provide and maintain the hardware infrastructure...</p>
      </section>

      <section id="requirements">
        <h4>Hardware Requirements</h4>
        <p>A Virtual Machine with 4 CPUs, 8GB of RAM and 40GB of disk space should be enough...</p>
      </section>

      <section id="costs">
        <h4>Costs</h4>
        <p>No cost for BioData.pt associates. Budget on demand for other institutions.</p>
